04-24 19:33:12.366 I/NARR-STATE(27696): narrationState → Speaking(segment=NarrationSegment(id=poi_narration_1617930781458665, text=In 1970, the set of the television show ‘Bewitched’ relocated to Salem after a fire forced production out of its Hollywood studios. The city’s historic architecture and atmosphere proved a fitting backdrop for the show’s seventh season. To commemorate this connection, and the show’s 40th anniversary, TV Land gifted the city of Salem with this six-foot-tall bronze statue of Elizabeth Montgomery, who played the iconic Samantha Stephens.\n\nUnveiled in 2005, the statue quickly became a popular attraction and a symbol of Salem’s embrace of its pop-culture connections. Located on Essex Street, it offers a fun and whimsical counterpoint to the city’s more somber historical narratives, and continues to draw fans of the show from around the world., type=LONG_NARRATION, poiName=Bewitched Sculpture – Samantha Statue, voiceId=en-us-x-tpd-local, kind=POI, category=null, refId=poi_narration, isReplay=false)) (autoPlay=true, queueSize=1)
